space-before-keywords.description:
Description

This rule will enforce consistency of spacing before the keywordsif,else,for,while,do,switch,throw,try,catch,finally,with,break,continue,return,function,yield,classand variable declarations (let,const,var)
and label statements.

This rule takes one argument:"always"or"never". If"always"then the keywords
must be preceded by at least one space. If"never"then no spaces will be allowed before
the keywordselse,while(doâ€¦while),finallyandcatch. The default value is"always".

This rule will allow keywords to be preceded by an opening curly brace ({). If you wish to alter
this behavior, consider using theblock-spacingrule.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule with the default"always"option:

/*eslint space-before-keywords: ["error", "always"]*/

if (foo) {
    // ...
}else {}

const foo = 'bar';let baz = 'qux';

var qux =function bar () {}

function bar() {
    if (foo) {return; }
}

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule with the default"always"option:

/*eslint space-before-keywords: ["error", "always"]*/

if (foo) {
    // ...
} else {}

(function() {})();

<Foo onClick={function bar() {}} />

for (let foo of ['bar', 'baz', 'qux']) {}

